The Federal Operations Unit Zone ‘A’ of the Nigeria Customs Service (NCS) said it intercepted goods with a total duty paid value of N20.8 billion in 2020.
 
Ag. Controller, DC Usman Yahaya, in a statement, said the unit also raked in about N1.7 billion through its anti-smuggling activities the same year, adding that it remains resolute to the course of protecting the national security and economy.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .